error.verbose:
The scope of the variable &#039;func&#039; can be reduced. Warning: Be careful when fixing this message, especially when there are inner loops. Here is an example where cppcheck will write that the scope for &#039;i&#039; can be reduced:
void f(int x)
{
    int i = 0;
    if (x) {
        // it&#039;s safe to move &#039;int i = 0;&#039; here
        for (int n = 0; n &lt; 10; ++n) {
            // it is possible but not safe to move &#039;int i = 0;&#039; here
            do_something(&amp;i);
        }
    }
}
When you see this message it is always safe to reduce the variable scope 1 level.

